The skin, skull, and skeleton are in good condition. Frozen tissues are deposited at the Royal Ontario Museum (
F 50445
).

Rostrum is slender; has a well developed anterior notch in the nasals; postorbital processes moderately developed; paraoccipital processes poorly developed; two infraorbital foramina present; posterior border of hard palate ‘V’-shaped (
Fig. 6
); fossa on the squamosal root of the zygomatic arch absent; and paraoccipital and paracondylar processes poorly developed.
